<docs>
	<doc for="ActionType.Undo">
		<summary>
			<para> The action can be undone.</para>
			<para>An <see langword="Undo"/> type action unit will
    revert the values previously changed by the action unit to the original values on the next call
    to the action unit's <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IActionUnit.DoAction"/> method.</para>
		</summary>
	</doc>
	<doc for="ActionType.Redo">
		<summary>
			<para> The action can be redone.</para>
			<para>A <see langword="Redo"/> type action unit
    can redo the changes of the undone action with the next call to the
    action unit's <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IActionUnit.DoAction"/> method.</para>
		</summary>
	</doc>
	<doc for="ActionType">
		<summary>
			<para> Specifies
      identifiers that indicate an action unit's undo or redo state attribute.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>These identifiers are used to indicate the current undo or redo state of an object that
      implements the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IActionUnit"/> interface. Objects that implement the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IActionUnit"/> interface provide support for the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IUndoService"/> interface, an action undo and redo service.
      The <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IActionUnit"/> and <see cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IUndoService"/>
      interfaces have been designed so that action units can be undone and redone
      after the action first occurs.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.ComponentModel.Design.IActionUnit"/>
	</doc></docs>
